cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.IR. 

The paper is about Spoken Language Understanding (SLU), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) that deals with understanding spoken language. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of supervised learning methods, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The semi-automatic procedure used to derive the dataset involves text processing, which could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates various open source and commercial systems, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
